(49, 'Dr. G. SUBASH CHANDRABOSE', 'Gandhi.K', '1982-05-12', '9942260031', '9942260031', 'subashstat@gmail.com', 'vinoth R', 'Azhagappnagar,   manjakuppam,Cuddlore', 'GH oppsity', 'Cuddlore', 'Tamil Nadu', 607001, 'india', 'G. Subash chandrabose', 2147483647, ' IOB', ' THAVALAKUPPAM', ' IOBA0001644', 'DNVPS7633J', 'TO ASSESS THE MANPOWER IN INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT THROUGH STO', 'Subash chandra bose', 'English', 'Academics', 30, '1', '1', '', '', '<p>Dr. Vinoth Raman, Assistant Professor from Imam Abdul Rahman Bin Faisal University, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia (KSA); with a demonstrated history of working in the higher education Institution. Skilled in Bio-Statistics, Statistical Software, Stochastic Modelling and Survival Analysis. Strong educational professionals with sound knowledge in research have a Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) in Statistics. Online teaching experience from Texila American University, as a subject matter expert for three years. Consultant to P.G and PhD students for their research activities. Published more than 50 articles and 4 books. Editorial Board Member in reputed journals. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 7829, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(50, 'Suaihiamthanliu pamei', 'Namchingdin pamei', '1993-08-24', '8376077391', '', 'suaihiamthanliupamei@gmail.com', 'Lugunliu pamei', ' flat no 577 DDA SFS flats pocket 1 sector 22 dwarka', 'New Mount Carmel junior ', 'New Delhi', 'Delhi', 110077, 'India', 'Suaihiamthanliu pamei ', 2147483647, 'Punjab National Bank', 'Dwarka (1434) south west delhi.', 'PUNB0143420', 'DDGPP5849L', 'JESUS AND ME ', 'SUAIHIAMTHANLIU PAMEI', 'English', 'Others', 2, '1', '1', '<p>I will be sending two photo&nbsp; for the book cover to put it&nbsp; on the front and at the back ..and I would like you to use the word for my title white or silver colour .. I don&#39;t want you to darken picture if you want to, then&nbsp; consult with me first .&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><span class=\"marker\">I&#39;am able to write this book because the holy spirit is partnering with me ,the&nbsp; holy spirit is reminding us&nbsp; &nbsp;what the lord had already said in the Bible as well as to us .&nbsp; Let&#39;s grow together and let&#39;s&nbsp; be obedient&nbsp; by doing all the things that he has said .</span></p>\r\n', '<p>My name is&nbsp; SUAIHIAMTHANLIU PAMEI form tamenglong , Manipur , India .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>My profession is singing .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>My hobbies are ,shopping, fishing, singing and reading .</p>\r\n', 34602, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(51, 'Sub (Retd) Vikram Singh Chauhan', 'Man Singh Chauhan', '1961-03-03', '7976523672', '9649555509', 'vs.chauhan1961@gmail.com', 'Geeta Devi', '25A Ganpati Nagar Nangal Jaisa Bohra Niwaru Road Jhotwara Ja', 'Ganpati Nagar Nangal Jaisa Bohra Niwaru Road ', 'Jaipur', 'Rajasthan', 302012, 'India', 'Vikram Singh Chauhan', 2147483647, 'State Bank of India', 'Jaipur Cantt', 'SBIN0005708', 'AEUPC1385G', 'Sahi Soch', 'Sub (Retd) Vikram Singh Chauhan', 'Hindi', 'Fiction', 10, '1', '1', '<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Basically Control and Prevent Suside cases in Army and Families due to stress.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>&ldquo;Sahi Soch&rdquo; Help to us Success in Life.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Sahi Soch help to our smoothly routine work.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Decrease stress in workplace and during duty.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Helpful to SIS Security Guards they are perform duty in stress.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Sahi Soch helpful to&rdquo; Sahi Soch&rdquo; correct decision in different situations.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>For upgrade to our moral and Motivation.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Helpful to avoid quarrel /dispute in our life.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Cover&nbsp; our financially management.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Helpful to achieve better Health and wealth. </strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Motivational and a Army Jawan Photoin Back Cover.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>To under stand that we are enjoy a freedom Life</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>We show a photo of a SIS Security guard for batter success.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p><strong>Roman</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Main ek bahut hi sadharan pariwar se hu, mere pita Rajasthan police me sewarat the. Rajasthan alwar se B.com ki padhai karte karte main 31 Dec 2080 ko Army ki 11 Machanised Infantry Battalion me Bharti ho gaya. Aneko parishiti se jujhate huye Subedar pad par kaam karte hue 31 dec 2010 ko sena se retire ho gaya. Retirement ke kuchh hi samay baad CRPF me as a Inspector Srinagr {Kashmir } me sewa karne ka avsar mila. Aur Hal hi me main SIS (Security and Intelligence Services Limited) me Training Manager ke pad par karyarat hu. 2007 me Army ke Jawanon me badhati hui stress ke karan suside case hone lagi tab mere dimag me aaya ki ek aisi pustak likhi jaye jo is stress ko kam kare aur Sabhi jawano ko Motivated kar sake.aaj bhi main ye kaam SIS company me kar raha hu.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 14069, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://bfcgroup.in/assets/asf_profile_pic/9e1bf979-87fe-407e-8acf-867d82ba6d42.jfif', ''),
(52, 'Sushil kumar', 'Shri. R. Dassgupta', '1949-12-24', '9910014040', '9818786969', 'sushilkumar@stjudesacademy.org', 'Sudha Kumar', '“EDEN” 551, Sector 14, Gurgaon  Near Water Tank   GURGAON   ', 'Near Water Tank', 'GURGAON', 'HARYANA', 122001, 'India', 'Sushil Kumar', 2147483647, 'HDFC BANK', 'Sector 14, Gurgaon', 'HDFC0000090', 'AKZPK5214H', 'Tanhaeeyaan…', '“Suweda” Dehlvi', 'Hindi', 'Poetry', 35, '1', '2', '<p><strong>&ldquo;Tanhaeeyan&rdquo; is a collection of poems reflecting the feelings, emotions &amp; the state of mind of the poet that he finds himself to be in when he is alone and all by himself with his own being in his own world.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Poet by nature is a loner and does not believe in sharing with others or revealing his painful experiences or sadness he has faced in life. He doesn&rsquo;t like to show or showcase the hardships or struggles he has faced in life as a growing young man. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Instead; he finds solace in his lonely surroundings and pours down all the sadness of his lonely existence on a piece of paper in the form of poems and thus draws strength from his own loneliness to carry on with life; while presenting a normal lifestyle of a successful man with no worries to the people around him &ndash; the same people he never shared any of his sorrows with!</strong></p>\r\n', '', '<p><strong>Born and brought up in the narrow lanes of Old Delhi&ndash;6,&nbsp; as a poet he started his journey at a very young age of 12 years by composing couplets in Urdu and gradually started writing ghazals &amp; Nazms with no guidance or help from any other person or poet. He did not show his creations to anybody for corrections since writing poems came to him very naturally.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Professionally; he comes with a background of thirty five years of long service at a large Foreign Diplomatic Mission in New Delhi. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Presently he lives in Gurgaon and as a Motivational Speaker &amp; Trainer manages his training institute called </strong><strong>School Of Civilities &amp; Protocol</strong><strong>; which is a self-development &amp; motivational training wing of </strong><strong>St. Jude&rsquo;s Academy of Education &amp; Training</strong><strong>; founded by the poet.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>He is also a Trained Education Agent of Cambridge English Assessment, UK &amp; a PTE Partner of Pearson/PTE for teaching English as a second language to&nbsp; young aspirants who wish to go abroad for overseas education or employment.</strong></p>\r\n', 12197, NULL, NULL, 'sushil_kumar.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/sushil_kumar.jpg', NULL);
INSERT INTO `chorus_asf` (`asf_id`, `asf_authorname`, `asf_fathername`, `asf_dob`, `asf_contact`, `asf_altercontact`, `asf_email`, `asf_nomineename`, `asf_address`, `asf_landmark`, `asf_city`, `asf_state`, `asf_pincode`, `asf_country`, `asf_accountholdername`, `asf_accountno`, `asf_bankname`, `asf_branch`, `asf_ifsc`, `asf_panno`, `asf_booktitle`, `asf_appearbookname`, `asf_mslanguage`, `asf_bookgenre`, `asf_imagecount`, `asf_msstatus`, `asf_booksize`, `asf_synopsis`, `asf_blurb`, `asf_authorbio`, `lead_id`, `pan_upload`, `cheque_upload`, `profile_pic`, `profile_pic_url`, `upload_data`) VALUES
(53, 'Shyamal Bhattacharjee ', 'Late Jiban Chandra Bhattacharjee ', '1959-07-06', '9980794880', '9845647969', 'shyamalbjp01@gmail.com', 'Sagarika Bhattacharjee ', 'Mahaveer Laurel Flat 115  2nd Main, Manjunath Extension , Ko', 'Manjunath Extension', 'Bangalore', 'Karnataka', 560076, 'India ', 'Shyamal Bhattacharjee ', 2147483647, 'Bank Of Baroda ', 'MSRS NAGAR , Karnataka ', 'BARBOBYRASA', 'ackpb3866F', 'Golden Quotes On Inspiration, Sorrow , Peace and Life ', 'Shyamal Bhattacharjee ', 'English', 'Non-Fiction', 0, '1', '2', '<p><strong>It is attached to the soft copy of the book Hence would&nbsp; not like to add any lines further&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>It is attached to the soft copy of the book Hence would&nbsp; not like to add any lines further&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Born at West Chirimiri Colliery on July 6th 1959 and educated at Carmel Convent School ,&nbsp; Bishrampur at Chhattisgarh and at C.C.B.H.S.S. , Jabalpur the author completed his Graduation in 1982 from Nagpur University , studying Science and later acquiring a Degree in Arts. He then had served as a Sub-Editor ( Sports ) at Hitavada, but gave up his job to complete his studies in Management ( M.B.A ) in 1984. He was a commentator for the All India radio at Nagpur on Hockey and Football and played Cricket, Hockey and Football for the W.C.L clubs at Nagpur. He also was a Student Leader at Nagpur . He has authored three books which have done exceedingly well at the national and International stage. He also maintains a world famous blog page BHATTACHARJEE SHYAMAL Blogger which has received WORLD WIDE attention . </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 28410, NULL, NULL, 'Pic.JPG', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Pic.JPG', NULL),
(54, 'Anil', 'Raghunath', '1961-02-07', '9686456217', '9686456217', 'anil.dhasal@gmail.com', 'Sunanda', '13 Rosewood Sahyognagar', 'Garkhrda', 'Aurangabad', 'Maharashtra', 431005, 'India', 'Anil Ragunath Dhasal', 2147483647, 'Axis Bank Ltd', 'Aurangabad', 'UTIB0000165', 'AAUPD1482B', 'Shape Your Children to beat the rat race', 'Anil Dhasal', 'English', 'Children Book', 10, '1', '2', '<p>The theme of this book is to guide parents and children perticularly teen ager the necessary of inculcate ten habits since childhood to beat the rat race.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mispewrceptions,need &amp; urgency of enculcating these ten habits are explained through stories</p>\r\n', '<p>Now a days due to bumbarment of various good and bad info via various media adding confusions in paraents&#39; mind ,whether they shall provide exposer of these media to their children or not.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to author, if we close the door to prevent damaging info from coming in , then from where the constructive ifo will come ?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We shall keep door open for information coing through various media with some vigillance</p>\r\n', '<p>Author is an Engineer by profession ,enriched with experience more than 40 years in Industries . He worked with people of various mind set,culture from various class &amp; mass of societry . Authors also conduct seminars on Personality Development and productivity development .</p>\r\n', 34597, NULL, NULL, 'Self.png', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Self.png', NULL),
(55, 'Aditya Nagrath', 'Sunil Kumar', '1988-08-19', '9781993156', '9417213282', 'adityanagrath@yahoo.com', 'Kanwaldeep Kaur', '4857-A, New Sunny Enclave, Sector 125', 'Near Chhabra Hospital', 'Kharar', 'Punjab', 140301, 'India', 'Aditya Nagrath', 2147483647, 'State Bank of India', 'Medical Institute, PGI, Chandigarh', 'SBIN0001524', 'AJDPN2320E', 'Samaj Seva ka Virus', 'Aditya Nagrath', 'English', 'Others', 10, '1', '1', '<p>My fron cover is ready. I will share the pdf on mail</p>\r\n', '<p>Life is indeed a lesson. It teaches us so many things - about success, feelings, happiness. Amongst everything, what it never ceases to teach is about hardwork and kindness. Samaj Seva ka Virus is an amalgamation of thoughts and experiences. It includes some insightful and wise words about goals, initiatives, perseverance, empowerment and philanthropy to name a few.</p>\r\n', '<p>Aditya Nagrath is a Medical Technologist in Department of Radio-diagnosis and Imaging, PGI, Chandigarh since 2010. He completed graduation from PGI, Chandigarh in 2008 and post graduation from PGI, Chandigarh in 2016 and currently pursuing doctorate in allied health sciences.<br />\r\nHe is Founder member and General Secretary at Sankalp NGO, Chandigarh since 2014. He has been awarded for his contribution for motivating others towards blood donation by Rotary and Blood Bank Society Resource Centre, Chandigarh.<br />\r\nHe&rsquo;s also a Founder member of Sankalp Siksha Kendra, a free school for the underprivileged kids at Kansal village, Punjab.<br />\r\nHe is also a motivational speaker at various events in encouraging youth towards social services.</p>\r\n', 35863, NULL, NULL, 'Aditya.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Aditya.jpg', NULL),
(56, 'ANKUR MONDAL', 'JADUPATI MONDAL', '2021-10-24', '902425789', '9477367494', 'mondal.ankur@gmail.com', 'Mrs. Dipshikha Mondal', '4B/4, Urban Sabujayan Jagatipota, kolkata- 700099', 'Calcutta Public School', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', 700099, 'India', 'Ankur Mondal', 2147483647, 'SBI', 'Madurdaha Krishnakunja', 'SBIN0016639', 'AWTPM6943R', 'Anarjo', 'Ankur Mondal', 'Hindi', 'Fiction', 3, '2', '2', '<p>This is a story of so called &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;; those are not at all interested in civilized world. It is n fiction adventure, in remote jungle surrounded by hill area of some tribes. In general the tribes use their long -knife, flambeau, bow and venomous-arrow, sword, long- spear, lance, stone hammer etc for their own protection. Also they use ropes made by many creepers of jungle. They don&rsquo;t use clothes for cladding themselves. Few of them use bark or plant leaves for clothing. One mentor is always there, who is called &lsquo;Pradhan (leader) of the jungle&rsquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the present leader is not actually tribe by birth. He is a civilized, but poor human being, came here for job from North East India. He has a sister also along with him in the forest office.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is all in all to take emergency decision for welfare of jungle. He is also considered as priest of the jungle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The jungle is divided into two parts by a waterfall. One side is safe for living; another side is dense and not safe. In the living area of jungle there is a tall and huge uncut one stone, treated as The GOD of the jungle. And the worship of The GOD is done by the priest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All animals and living beings are there, in the jungle. Like- omnivorous, carnivorous, reptiles, fishes, mammals, birds etc. All are free to move unless they hurt anybody for their hunger. It is considered that all living and nonliving beings of the jungle are connected to each other directly or indirectly by the blessing of The GOD.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are some certain rules, made by the leader to keep peace in the jungle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One &lsquo;Arjo&rsquo;, (civilized) forest officer will come here and gradually he will fall in love of the jungle. He is brave heart and will save an &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;, (tribe) child from the mouth of the tiger. Then a holy &ldquo;Homa Joggo&rdquo; (sacred fire) will happen by the priest, in front of The Jungle GOD, the large stone, to destroy all evils from the jungle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that, the recent forest officer, very easily, will win the heart of everybody, even of the leader. At the end this story, the forest officer will leave the job and become the leader of the jungle. And he will build a non-paid school for tribe children, a non-paid hospital for everybody within the forest and will totally separate the jungle from the outsiders without any emergency cases.</p>\r\n', '<p>This is a story of so called &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;; those are not at all interested in civilized world. It is n fiction adventure, in remote jungle surrounded by hill area of some tribes. In general the tribes use their long -knife, flambeau, bow and venomous-arrow, sword, long- spear, lance, stone hammer etc for their own protection. Also they use ropes made by many creepers of jungle. They don&rsquo;t use clothes for cladding themselves. Few of them use bark or plant leaves for clothing. One mentor is always there, who is called &lsquo;Pradhan (leader) of the jungle&rsquo;. All animals and living beings are there, in the jungle. Like- omnivorous, carnivorous, reptiles, fishes, mammals, birds etc. All are free to move unless they hurt anybody for their hunger. It is considered that all living and nonliving beings of the jungle are connected to each other directly or indirectly by the blessing of The GOD. In the jungle there is a tall and huge uncut one stone, treated as The GOD of the jungle. And the worship of The GOD is done by the priest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is all in all to take emergency decision for welfare of jungle. He is also considered as priest of the jungle. There are some certain rules, made by the leader to keep peace in the jungle. But the present leader is not at all tribe by birth. He is a civilized, but poor human being, came here for job from North East India. He has a sister also along with him in the forest office. One &lsquo;Arjo&rsquo;, (civilized) forest officer will come here and gradually he will fall in love of the jungle. He is brave heart and will save an &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;, (tribe) child from the mouth of the tiger. Then a holy &ldquo;Homa Joggo&rdquo; (sacred fire) will happen by the priest, in front of The Jungle GOD, the large stone, to destroy all evils from the jungle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The jungle is divided into two parts by a waterfall. One side is safe for living; another side is dense and not safe. But with the help of the leader the officer will visit the other part of the waterfall. And they discovered that that side is totally captured by the poacher. After that the officer along with local police arrested all those thieves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that, the recent forest officer, very easily, will win the heart of everybody, even of the leader. At the end this story, the forest officer will leave the job and become the leader of the jungle. And he will build a non-paid school for tribe children, a non-paid hospital for everybody within the forest and will totally separate the jungle from the outsiders without any emergency cases.</p>\r\n', '<p>ANKUR MONDAL, was born in a native village of West Bengal in 1981. From his very childhood he loved nature- free air, open sky, animals, birds, fishes etc. He studied, Masters in Computer Science in 2007, from WBUT, West Bengal. In his career, he has been teaching, giving training and doing some research works in different fields, related to computer science. He completed Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning certification, successfully in the year of 2019. But, at the beginning of 2020, the worldwide pandemic changed his mind totally, due to live and let live others. He started to thing several alternatives apart from AIML. He become the intense disciple of Lord Sri Sri Ramakrishna and started to realize the ultimate truth of the life. Now he tries to enlighten the spirit of the life through different type of writings.</p>\r\n', 11058, NULL, NULL, 'IMG_2741.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/IMG_2741.jpg', NULL),
(57, 'Anuradha Kanakameti', 'Veeraiah Kanakameti', '1978-06-24', '7678477282', '9868257435', 'anusamarth@gmail.com', 'M.Gangadharappa', 'Flat No.B2-103, Type 4, Delhi Govt. Officer’s Quarters, Haid', 'Opposite to DA Block', 'Delhi', 'Delhi', 110088, 'India', 'Mandlem Anuradha', 2147483647, 'Canara Bank', 'Delhi Pitampura Branch', 'CNRB0001565', 'AZQPA4725P', 'English Grammar Learn & Communicate', 'Anuradha Kanakameti', 'English', 'Academics', 5, '1', '2', '<p><strong>This English Grammar book contains parts of Speech, Noun, Pronoun, Verb, Adverb, Adjective, Preposition, Conjunction and Interjection in detail with definitions. Examples and Exercises at the end of each topic were provided for better understanding and practice. Emphasis given on Sentence formation and its kinds, Common mistakes in English, Vocabulary (word Power). The letters sound for communication i.e &nbsp;Diphthongs, Determiners, Written Communication Skills, Antonyms and Synonyms were covered in detail. Discussed different forms of Letter Writing that includes formal and informal. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Salient Features of this book</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Each chapter covers the concepts with clear explanation</li>\r\n	<li>The basics in English are introduced in simplest possible terms</li>\r\n	<li>Examples are supported with plenty of illustrations for better understanding</li>\r\n	<li>The book perfectly suits for, the school going children, college students and all those who are keen to learn the English Grammar.</li>\r\n	<li>The book facilitates to communicate confidently in English</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This book sharpens written as well as spoken English skills</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>English Grammar Learn &amp; Communicate, ensures the students to gain comprehensive knowledge and make them confident while communicating. This book contains lot of examples and exercises to thoroughly develop their skills. The book is organized in systematic fashion to learn the concepts as easily as possible.</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Anuradha Kanakameti living in Delhi. I did my Schooling and Graduation (B.sc in PCM) from Hyderabad, Telangana, India. &nbsp;Obtained Master&rsquo;s Degree in MCA from Kakatiya University, Warangal, Telangana. Presently working as an Academic Counsellor at IGNOU, New Delhi. Since my childhood, I am passionate about writing books in order to share my knowledge. My Source of Inspiration and motivation is my Guru, who is my Mother. I have done Diploma in Spoken English course from prestigious Vivekananda Institute of Languages, Ramakrishna Math, Hyderabad. The objective of this book is to make the students to gain knowledge and to build strong grammatical skills in English. My book will be useful to school-going children, College going Students, and for all those who are keen to learn English Grammar.</strong></p>\r\n', 13217, NULL, NULL, 'Anuradha.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Anuradha.jpg', NULL),
(58, 'MARIAN McGRATH BURN', 'S.P.McGrath', '1959-08-21', '7800011445', '9140046453', 'mburn218@gmail.com', 'Ashley Burn (Husband)', '8, Maqbara Square,  Hazratgunj, Lucknow', 'Opposite Halwasiya Market, Hazratgunj', 'Lucknow', 'Uttar Pradesh ', 226001, 'India', 'Marian Patricia Burn', 2147483647, 'State Bank of India', 'M.G.Marg (Lucknow)', 'SBIN0006496', 'AHWPM5547P', 'NEWNESS OF LIFE', 'MARIAN BURN', 'English', 'Others', 0, '1', '1', '<p>NEWNESS OF LIFE, could best be described as a &#39;new day&#39; and can be illustrated by a rising sun, glistening on a long road.&nbsp; It talks about a new way of living by faith and not by sight, which means it describes how a christian&#39;s life should be lived according to the teachings of Jesus.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It could also be illustrated by a beautiful, colorful butterfly breaking out of a cocoon and fluttering its wings and flying away to live its short life in this world, spreading its joy and beauty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It can be expressed by a flower opening up its petals in all its freshness and beauty.&nbsp; Newness of Life is Bible based and&nbsp;teaches&nbsp;us how we should walk now that Jesus has saved us&nbsp;and set us free from sin, death and from the hands of the enemy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>NEWNESS OF LIFE is a compilation of 101 meditations of the&nbsp;heart.&nbsp; The content is Scriptural and the language simple.&nbsp;These&nbsp;reflections are based on&nbsp;Bible&nbsp;verses put together thematically, as best&nbsp;as one&nbsp;could, in order to&nbsp;elucidate&nbsp;a given topic. They were originally written during&nbsp;the lockdown year 2020 through 2021 in random order, but were&nbsp;compiled&nbsp;later.&nbsp; Some of the topics include Repentance, Holiness, Faith, Divine Healing, Salvation, Praise and God&#39;s Eternal Word&nbsp;amongst others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was never&nbsp;intended for publishing, but it was a personal prayer journal that the author&nbsp;later decided&nbsp;to share with others.&nbsp; The Christian walk is not just terribly difficult, a path so rocky&nbsp;that many fall by the wayside,&nbsp;but it is down right&nbsp;&nbsp;impossible to achieve in one&#39;s&nbsp;own human strength. It is, however, simple and full of joy when we partner with &quot;the Helper,&quot; the Holy Spirit who abides in us. The purpose for&nbsp;this&nbsp;work, therefore, is to address some of the doubts that haunt us, and the lies of this world that cling&nbsp;to us from our past life. It is the Truth&nbsp;alone that&nbsp;sets us free and enables us to live&nbsp;as Jesus taught us.&nbsp;&nbsp;So NEWNESS OF LIFE&nbsp;is intended&nbsp;to encourage the brethren&nbsp;to walk by Faith and not by sight&nbsp;in the &quot;New Life&quot; we have in Christ Jesus.&nbsp; He has saved us from sin, death and from the hands of the enemy by His own death on the Cross, and by His Resurrection from the dead. All Glory be to Jesus forever.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Marian Burn is an ordinary Christian, one that has given herself whole heartedly to the studying of God&rsquo;s Living Word.&nbsp; Having experienced the Grace of God, His abundance and His power in her own life, she has a repository of experiences from which she writes and teaches.&nbsp; &nbsp;She has no formal training, no degrees from any Bible college or seminary,&nbsp; She has,&nbsp; however, studied God&rsquo;s Word over the last 15 years or more and realizes that she has only begun to scratch the surface. &nbsp;Her special interest is in the subject of Divine Healing and Health, which comes through the Cross of Christ, because she saw such a little knowledge on the subject in her local church and could feel the lowest levels of faith in Christians around her.&nbsp; In these Covid times, she wants &nbsp;people to know that despite all the pestilences that the world is seeing, we have a God much greater than Covid or any other virus and He has promised to preserve and heal us,&nbsp;because He loves us like no one else can.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 36255, NULL, NULL, 'Profile_Pic.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Profile_Pic.jpg', NULL),
(59, 'बंशीधर नाहरवाल', 'स्व. श्योजी राम', '1950-10-27', '9968255703', '7011177622', 'bdnaharwal@gmail.com', 'Gaurav Naharwal', 'K-74-A, Gali No 5', 'Opp. Deep Parmarth School, Puran Nagar Palam Colony', 'New Delhi', 'Delhi', 110077, 'India', 'Banshi Dhar', 2147483647, 'Axis Bank', 'Palam', 'UTIB0000132', 'AAOPD1354Q', '\'Gareeba ki Tijori', 'बंशीधर नाहरवाल', 'Hindi', 'Fiction', 0, '1', '3', '<p>उपन्यास का नायक गरीबा अत्यंत गरीब है और यह गरीबी उसके परिवार को पीढी दर पीढी मिलती आई है।वह अनुसूचित जाति का भी है&nbsp; और गरीबी के कारण पढाई लिखाई ना के बराबर है। साहुकार उन्हें हमेशा अपने चंगुल में फंसाकर रखता है। गरीबा कृषि कार्य करता है पर अधबंटाई पर क्यों कि उसके पास स्वयं की कृषि भूमि नहीं है। वह साहुकार के खेतों को ही जोतता है और फसल पर अधिकतर उपज अपने पास रख लेता है, कुछ तो अधबंटाई की और बाकी पुराने करते की भरपाई के रूप में। बेचारे गरीबा के पास कुछ नहीं बचता है और फिर साहुकार से ही अपने द्वारा पैदा किया अनाज उधारी में लेता है अर्थात कर्ज का भार और बढ़ जाता है। बाकी समय में कुछ मजदूरी भी कर लेता है वह एकाध पशु भी पालता है पर गरीबी से उबर ही नहीं पाता है। वैसे उसकी पत्नी भी मेहनती वह नेक औरत है, घर गृहस्थी के काम में लगी ही रहती है पर साहुकार के पंजे से परिवार मुक्त नहीं हो पा रहा है।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>इसके साथ ही परिवार कुछ अंधविश्वास में भी फंस जाता है, गांव का पंडित आये दिन कुछ न कुछ अनुष्ठान, पूजा पाठ करने की सलाह देता रहता है जिसमें कुछ खर्चा तो होता ही है।अभी उसके बाप दुखिया की मृत्यु हुई है जिसका भी भोज कराया गया, साहुकार से कर्ज लेना पड़ा।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>गरीबा की ही जाति का एक और परिवार है उसके गांव में जिसका लड़का पढ़ लिख कर कालेज में प्रवक्ता है। प्रवीण का बाप भी गरीब ही है, राजमिस्त्री का काम करता है पर बहुत ही समझदार है। उसका एकमात्र ध्येय अपने बच्चों को अच्छी शिक्षा दिलवाना रहा है और अब दूसरा बेटा भी इंजिनियरिंग की पढ़ाई कर रहा है और एकमात्र बेटी भी अध्यापन क्षेत्र में जाना चाहती है।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>गरीबा अब कुछ समय निकाल कर प्रवीण वह उसके पिताजी से सलाह लेता है और वे कुछ मार्ग दर्शन देते हैं। गरीबा का एक बेटा और एक बेटी है, दोनों बच्चे पढ़ाई में रुचि रखते हैं। गरीबा भी अब नयी सोच से आगे बढ़ने की ठान लेता है। साहुकार के अलावा दूसरे जमींदार की जमीन बंटाई पर लेकर खेती करता है जहां उसे ईमानदारी से अपना हिस्सा मिलता है। गरीबा ने भी अपने बेटे का नाम अपने बापू के कहने पर सूरज रखा है जो साहुकार के बेटे का भी नाम है।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>सूरज अपनी लग्न व मेहनत से हाई स्कूल परीक्षा जिले में सर्वाधिक अंक लेकर उत्तीर्ण होता है जिससे जिला प्रशासन से भी आगे की पढ़ाई के लिए कुछ सुविधाएं मिलती हैं, प्लस टू करते हुए उसको आई आई टी में प्रवेश मिलता है। प्रवीण उसे समय समय पर मार्गदर्शन देता रहा है और उसकी इंजीनियरिंग पूरी होने से पहले ही आशा से कई गुना अधिक का अंतरराष्ट्रीय कम्पनी में जॉब मिल जाता है, एक तरह से गरीबा की तिजोरी खुल जाती है, उसका भाग्य ही बदल जाता है।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>इसके बीच एक और बच्चे का वृतांत दिया है जो सफाई कर्मी जाति का है , गरीबी के कारण बढ़ नहीं पाता है। वह गांव छोड़ कर दिल्ली चला जाता है जहां वह एक स्कूल में साफ सफाई का कार्य करता है। उसकी मुलाकात एक कबाड़ इकट्ठा करने वाले से होती है जो स्कूल में रद्दी लेने आता है। यह लड़का कुछ सोचता है और फिर स्वयं ही स्कूल का कबाड़ बाजार में बेच कर कुछ मुनाफा कमाने लगता है। फिर वह एक छोटी सी दुकान किराए पर लेता है और कबाड़ियों से कबाड़ खरीद कर आगे बेचता है।इसी बीच उसकी मुलाकात कुछ बौद्ध अनुयायियों से होती है, वह उनके साथ बौद्ध विहार जाने लगता है और फिर उसकी उसमें आस्था बन जाती है आखिर में बौद्ध धर्म अपना ही लेता है।वह अपनी पढ़ाई भी करता है और ग्रेज्युवेशन कर लेता है। उसी बौद्ध समाज की पढ़ी लिखी लड़की से उसकी शादी भी होती है और उसका भी भाग्य चमक जाता है।</p>\r\n', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic;\">गरीबा की तिजोरी</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>लेखक</p>\r\n\r\n<p>बंशीधर नाहरवाल&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>बंशीधर नाहरवाल</p>\r\n\r\n<p>एम ए (अर्थशास्त्र)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>सेवा निवृत्त प्रथम श्रेणी अधिकारी</p>\r\n\r\n<p>रक्षा मंत्रालय, भारत सरकार</p>\r\n\r\n<p>साहित्यिक कृतियां:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>१. स्वामी विवेकानन्द के सेनफ्रासिसको में दिए गए ब्याख्यान &quot; बुद्धाज् मैसेज टू दी वर्ल्ड&quot; का हिंदी अनुवाद।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>२.बगुला भगत, स्वयं रचित कविताओं का संग्रह।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>३. आज का श्रवण कुमार, परिवारों में वृद्धों की हो रही दुर्दशा पर आधारित उपन्यास।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>४. Who tells you there is God - an illustrative book on almost all the religions of the world.</p>\r\n', 35605, NULL, NULL, 'f3e0ce67b385c700c37ce899b71b9eb9.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/f3e0ce67b385c700c37ce899b71b9eb9.jpg', NULL),
(60, 'Dr ARVIND AMAR', 'SRI PRABHU NANDAN SINGH', '1961-06-17', '9430675806', '7258090976', 'arvindamar1706@gmail.com', 'ANIKET AMAR', '202, AWADH VIHAR APARTMENT MULCHAND PATH, BAHADURPUR', 'NEAR SAI MANDIR', 'PATNA', 'BIHAR', 800020, 'INDIA', 'Arvind Amar', 2147483647, 'ICICI Bank', 'KANKARBAGH', 'ICIC0000307', 'ABQPA7623L', 'Dr Amar’s capsule for JAIIB ACCOUNTING & FINANCE FOR BANKERS', 'Dr Arvind Amar', 'English', 'Academics', 0, '1', '2', '<p>This book is for Bankers. There are three papers for the examination of JAIIB; one of them is <strong>Accounting &amp; Finance for Bankers. </strong>This is the course book based on syllabus and not a fiction book.</p>\r\n', '<p>This book aims to cater the needs of Banking professionals aiming to clear JAIIB by presenting the topics based on syllabus in simple and short way, easy to understand the Accounting and Finance for the aspirants of JAIIB. At the end of the chapter, Multiple Choice Questions have been given to help the readers to evaluate their understanding of the concepts. Some of the MCQs are solved with the view to make the concept more clear which makes the book unique and easy to understand.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Dr Arvind Amar (M.A,M.Com,PGDJMC,DTM,LL.B,DHLA,DMF,CAIIB,Ph.D.), Ex Chief Manager, DBGB have more than 35 years of Banking experience including 5 years as Faculty. Regularly conduct classes for JAIIB/CAIIB/ Bank Promotion. The books for all three papers for JAIIB have also been published in Hindi from SKYLARK Publication, New Delhi. He is pioneer of training.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 14359, NULL, NULL, 'Arvind_Amar_pic.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Arvind_Amar_pic.jpg', NULL),
(61, 'Bhagwati Prasad Goyal', 'Girwarlal Goyal', '1958-07-01', '9425160922', '6266635773', 'bpgoyal100@gmail.com', 'Ayush Goyal', '11-A, Janki Nagar, Chuna Bhatti, Kolar road', 'Near Suyash Hospital', 'Bhopal', 'Madhya Pradesh', 462042, 'India', 'Bhagwati Prasad Goyal', 2147483647, 'ICICI Bank', 'Bhopal Mpuvn', 'ICIC0006565', 'ADCPG5625N', 'Ek Engineer ki Kavya Vatika', 'Engineer B.P. Goyal - Jigyasu', 'Hindi', 'Poetry', 10, '2', '1', '<p>izFke n`&quot;V;k rks ;g fn[krk gS fd Jh xks;y dk jpuk lalkj fdruk foLr`r gSA firk vkSj Ekka dh vkjk/kuk ds ckn mUgksusa dksjksuk] eksckby] dkyk/ku] f&Oslash;dsV eSp] lkekftd fo&quot;kerk,a] mRlo vkSj vkuan tSls vusd fo&quot;k;ksa ij viuh dye lQyrk iwoZd pykbZ gSA fdlh O;fDr dk bl gn rd laosnu&#39;khy gksuk gh mls ,d lQy lkfgR;dkj ds :i esa LFkkfir djrk gSA dYiuk pkoyk ij fy[kh mudh dfork gesa ml Hkkjr dh csVh dh ;kn fnykrh gS ftlus varfj{k ds xw&lt;+ jgL;ksa dks &lt;w&lt;+us esa vius izk.kksa dk mRlxZ dj fn;kA iSlk dekus ls tks lqfo/kk,a feyh muds ckjs esa rks dfo us fy[kk gh gS ij ;g Hkh fy[kk gS fd xyr rjhds ls iSlk dekus esa vkRek dk ,d Hkkx eSyk gksdj] lnk ds fy;s lks x;kA</p>\r\n', '<p>izFke n`&quot;V;k rks ;g fn[krk gS fd Jh xks;y dk jpuk lalkj fdruk foLr`r gSA firk vkSj Ekka dh vkjk/kuk ds ckn mUgksusa dksjksuk] eksckby] dkyk/ku] f&Oslash;dsV eSp] lkekftd fo&quot;kerk,a] mRlo vkSj vkuan tSls vusd fo&quot;k;ksa ij viuh dye lQyrk iwoZd pykbZ gSA fdlh O;fDr dk bl gn rd laosnu&#39;khy gksuk gh mls ,d lQy lkfgR;dkj ds :i esa LFkkfir djrk gSA dYiuk pkoyk ij fy[kh mudh dfork gesa ml Hkkjr dh csVh dh ;kn fnykrh gS ftlus varfj{k ds xw&lt;+ jgL;ksa dks &lt;w&lt;+us esa vius izk.kksa dk mRlxZ dj fn;kA iSlk dekus ls tks lqfo/kk,a feyh muds ckjs esa rks dfo us fy[kk gh gS ij ;g Hkh fy[kk gS fd xyr rjhds ls iSlk dekus esa vkRek dk ,d Hkkx eSyk gksdj] lnk ds fy;s lks x;kA</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>dfo Jh Hkxorh izlkn xks;y dk tUe fot;iqj ftyk &#39;;ksiqj esa twu] 1959 esa gqvk FkkA gk;j lsds.Mjh rd f&#39;k{kk iw.kZ djus ds mijkUr ek/ko bULVhV