(62, 'धर्मभूषण पं. श्रीधर गौरहा', 'डा. भागीरथी गौरहा', '1967-04-17', '9424261917', '7987050212', 'shrigauraha@gmail.com', 'श्रीमती शारदा गौरहा', 'श्रीः विहार, सीपत रोड', 'राधिका विहार एवं सूर्या विहार मध्य', 'बिलासपुर', 'छत्तीसगढ', 495006, 'भारत', 'SHARDA GAURAHA', 2147483647, 'HDFC BANK', 'SEEPAT ROAD LINGIYADIH', 'HDFC0009640', 'BJCPG1555L', 'महाविद्या रत्नाकरः', 'धर्मभूषण पं. श्रीधर गौरहा', 'Hindi', 'Others', 21, '2', '3', '<p>मध्य में एक यंत्र के अंदर ह्रीं लिखा हो तथा उसके चारो ओर दश महाविद्या देवियों का फोटो सर्किल में हो । &nbsp;फ्रन्टपेज का कलर डार्क रेड एवं पीले रंग में हो । ग्रन्थ के पीछे सम्पादक/रचनाकर का फोटो सहित परिचय हो । अथवा फ्रन्ट में कुण्डलीनी शक्ति का फोटो हो और पीछे बैकग्राउन्ड में ब्रह्माण्ड का फोटो हो । बेहतर होगा कि इस विषय में फोन से चर्चा कर ली जाय। लिखकर बता पाना कठिन है। वाट्सऐप में आपको अपना नजरिया भेजा जा सकेगा।&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>बैक में रचनाकार का परिचन हो तो बेहतर है । साथ ही उनकी पूर्व प्रकाषित तीन पुस्तको का एक एक ऐड चाहिए।</p>\r\n', '<p>बाद में दे दिया जाएगाा ।</p>\r\n', 36189, NULL, NULL, 'SHRIDHAR_GAURAHA.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/SHRIDHAR_GAURAHA.jpg', NULL),
(63, 'K.K. SARASWAT', 'FATEH CHAND SARSWAT', '1980-07-08', '9258271390', '', 'sar_ict@rediffmail.com', 'GEETA', 'NEAR SHIV MANDIR, JHAJHAR, GB NAGAR', 'NEAR INTER COLLEGE', 'GREATER NOIDA', 'Uttar Pradesh', 203203, 'INDIA', 'KRISHNA KUMAR SARASWAT', 2147483647, 'SBI', 'JHAJHAR', 'SBIN000596', 'CJSPK65802', 'TALLY( FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING)', 'K.K. Saraswat, MCA', 'English', 'Academics', 100, '2', '2', '', '', '', 11373, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(64, 'Marian McGrath Burn', 'S.P.McGrath', '1959-08-21', '7800011445', '9140046453', 'mburn218@gmail.com', 'Ashley Burn (Husband)', '8, Maqbara Square,  Hazratgunj, Lucknow', 'Opposite Halwasiya Market, Hazratgunj', 'Lucknow', 'Uttar Pradesh', 226001, 'India', 'Marian Patricia Burn', 2147483647, 'State Bank of India', 'M.G.Marg (Lucknow)', 'SBIN0006496', 'AHWPM5547P', 'NEWNESS OF LIFE', 'MARIAN BURN', 'English', 'Others', 1, '1', '1', '<p>The purpose of this book is to bring light where there is darkness, and to increase faith, especially in these troubled times such as the world is going through now.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In&nbsp;fact in Christ He has already given us His own kind of Life, and those who believe in Him have already passed from death to Life that is eternal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NEWNESS OF LIFE, could best be described as a &#39;new day&#39; and can be illustrated by a rising sun, glistening on a long road.&nbsp; It talks about a new way of living by faith and not by sight, which means it describes how a christian&#39;s life should be lived according to the teachings of Jesus.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It could also be illustrated by a beautiful, colorful butterfly breaking out of a cocoon and flying away to live its short life in this world, spreading its joy and beauty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>NEWNESS OF LIFE is a compilation of 101 meditations of the&nbsp;heart.&nbsp; The content is Scriptural and the language simple.&nbsp;These&nbsp;reflections are based on&nbsp;Bible&nbsp;verses put together thematically, as best&nbsp;as one&nbsp;could in order to&nbsp;elucidate&nbsp;a given topic. They were originally written during&nbsp;the lockdown year 2020 through 2021 in random order but was compiled&nbsp;later.&nbsp; Some of the topics include Repentance, Holiness, Faith, Divine Healing, Salvation, Praise and God&#39;s Eternal Word&nbsp;amongst others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was never&nbsp;intended for publishing, but it was a personal prayer journal which the author&nbsp;later decided&nbsp;to share with others.&nbsp; The Christian walk is not just terribly difficult, but it is down right&nbsp;&nbsp;impossible to achieve in one&#39;s&nbsp;own human strength. It is however, simple and full of joy when we partner with &quot;the Helper,&quot; the Holy Spirit who abides in us. The purpose for&nbsp;this&nbsp;work therefore, is to address some of the doubts that haunt us, and the lies of this world that cling&nbsp;to us from our past life. It is the Truth&nbsp;alone that&nbsp;sets us free and enables us to live&nbsp;as Jesus taught us.&nbsp;&nbsp;So NEWNESS OF LIFE&nbsp;is intended&nbsp;to encourage Christians to walk by Faith not by sight&nbsp;in the &quot;New Life&quot; we have in Christ Jesus.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About the Author</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Marian Burn is an ordinary Christian, one that enjoys studying God&rsquo;s &nbsp;Word.&nbsp; Having experienced the Grace of God, His abundance and His power in her own life, she has a repository of experiences from which she writes and teaches.&nbsp; She has no formal training, no Degrees from any Bible college or seminary.&nbsp; However, she loves God&rsquo;s Word &nbsp;more than anything else and realizes that she has only begun to scratch the surface.&nbsp; The purpose of this book is to bring light where there is darkness, and to increase faith, especially in troubled times such as the world is going through now.&nbsp; Her special interest is in the subject of Divine Healing and Health, which comes through the Cross of Christ, because she saw such a little knowledge on the subject in her local church and could feel the lowest levels of faith in Christians around her.&nbsp; In these Covid times she felt it was necessary for people to know that despite all the pestilences that the world is seeing, we have a God who is much greater and One who has promised to preserve and heal us, One who loves us like no one else can.</p>\r\n', 36255, NULL, NULL, 'Profile_Pic1.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Profile_Pic1.jpg', NULL),
(65, 'DR. NISARG CHANDRAKANT JOSHI', 'MR. CHANDRAKANT JOSHI', '1989-10-05', '9265493598', '9408844575', 'drncj20@gmail.com', 'MR. CHANDRAKANT JOSHI', 'C-46, MANIDHAR VILLAGE BEHIND S.T WORKSHOP BECHARAJI, DIST.-', 'BEHIND S.T WORKSHOP', 'DIST.- MEHSANA', 'GUJARAT', 384210, 'INDIA', 'MR. NISARG CHANDRAKANT JOSHI', 2147483647, 'STATE BANK OF INDIA', 'BECHARAJI', 'SBIN0032156', 'ALMPJ8287F', 'Fundamentals of Electrocardiografía (ECG) with Arduino UNO', 'DR. N.C.JOSHI', 'English', 'Academics', 26, '1', '3', '<p>An Electrocardiogram (ECG) is used to monitor the heart.&nbsp; The body surface is recorded with ECG signals, and is a weak bipolar low frequency signal. A normal ECG signal&rsquo;s frequency range is 0.05-100Hz. Several noises such as power line noises, patient &ndash;electrode motion artifacts, baseline wandering, electrode contact noises and chest muscles of the EMG signals.&nbsp; It can enhance prevention and early diagnosis capability; improve patient condition, mobility, and security by continuous monitoring of heart. The device should be wearable or implantable inside the body to allow continuos monitoring of the ECG signal. Therefore it needs to be small, and the fewest disturbances from surrounding interference and other human body signals are possible. It causes the moderns to have the problem of cardiovascular disease, due to poor diet and too much pressure. For some initial stage of chronic cardiovascular diseases, it feels palpitations, dizziness and other symptoms, making it are easy for moderns to overlook the onset of the symptoms and lose first treatment. Nonetheless, some problems may have happened when the device is smaller. There&rsquo;s power consumption and high reliability in detection. This is introduces the Compressive Sensing Technique using Arduino Uno processor along With ECG Signals. Arduino is a platform which is open-source. Arduino is used for the electronic program and constructing. It can get information and sent it to most devices. The board is programming using hardware called Arduino Uno circuit board and software program. Heart Rate Variability (HRV) tends to monitor heart rate variations and can be an indicator of myocardial infarction, representing the physiological mechanisms of sympathetic nervous and parasympathetic control.&nbsp; The Arduino Uno is a microcontroller module, and it offers high-performance, it was a microcontroller based on AVR RISC. The device works from1.8- 5.5 volt. Compressive sensing is a method for signal processing.&nbsp; In the compressive sensing technique, the sparse signal is used and reconstructed from incomplete measurements, and it contains inadequate volume of information. It can be done if the signal with an ortho normal basis is in sparse representation. In that storage space and transmission times compression is significant. Therefore, for efficient storage and telemedicine applications, ECG data compression is important, and signal transmission is necessary. In sparse coding, linear-systems, multiplexing, and sparse sampling, compressive sensitive technique is used. It is utilized in the many innovative CS-enhanced approaches for signal processing. The Arduino Uno processor receives the signals obtained from the AD8232 sensor. The received signal will usually contain noise. Hence, compression of the ECG signal becomes a necessity where pre-processing of the received ECG signal is performed. The method proposed for Compressive Sensing is the Sparse based Discrete Walsh Hadamard Transform (SDWHT). After receiving the compressed signal out from the Arduino processor, the original ECG signal is reconstructed using the inverse SDWHT technique. The reconstructed ECG signal is displayed by three display units namely, Serial plotter, Personal Computer, and a Bluetooth module. The reconstructed ECG signal is sent to the PC installed with MATLAB. Then the P-QRS-T peak detection is performed in MATLAB. After finding the peaks of the reconstructed ECG signal, feature extraction is done with the help of Sparse feature learning technique. The Feature matrix obtained from the sparse feature learning is used in training the neural network for classification. Multi-layer Perceptron based Feed Forward Neural Network is considered for the classification of the ECG signals. The following are the classes considered for this research implementation such as normal, Premature Ventricular Contractions, Ventricular Tachycardia, Idioventricular Rhythm and Ventricular Flutter. The proposed classification model is tested for its performance, accuracy, sensitivity, f-score and error rate.</p>\r\n', '<p>The concept of this book is ECG signals- Electrocardiography is connected with Arduino UNO- microcontroller.<strong> </strong>This book demonstrates how our heart waves can be connected to a microcontroller. What kind of obstruction or change occurs in the wave according to the different changes of the atmosphere can be known from this book. The ECG Signal plays an important role in the diagnosis of heart diseases and disorders. An ECG is a significant physiological signal for diagnosis of cardiac disease. Modern usage of monitoring devices with electrocardiogram is increasing. Huge storage space and large quantities of data are that, and ECG compression is required for efficient storage and it has been extracted from a medical database. Aninteresting research line focuses on transforming the original one-dimensional waveforms of the ECG into two-dimensional information, followed by a processing stage using image processing tools. Many cardiac abnormalities can be observed with the aid of an ECG interpretation including inadequate blood flow, heart muscle death due to coronary thrombosis and heart muscle enlargement. Arduino can be used to for the development of interactive objects, taking inputs to control outputs. It is connected to the Arduino hardware to communicate and upload sketches. Arduino can read information from input devices such as Trimmer(potentiometer), Antenna, Sensors, e.t.c, and can also send data to the output devices such as Speakers, LED, DC motor, LCD Screen, e.t.c. User communities are groups of people using a given product, the Arduino in this case. So, the design has been enhanced, and it helps drive the Arduino board for direction to future.</p>\r\n', '<p>Dr. Nisarg Chandrakant Joshi is Assistant Professor, Physics &amp; Nodal Officer of Ratnamani Science &amp; Commerce College, Becharaji, Mehsana, Gujarat. He has completed his under graduation in Electronics from Veer Narmad South Gujarat University, Surat in 2011, and his post graduation in Electronics &amp; Communication from Sardar Patel University, V. V. Nagar in 2013. He has completed M.Phil in Electronics &amp; Communication from UNS Institute of Engineering &amp; Technology, in 2014. He has completed Ph.D in Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering under guidance of Prof. Dr. C. Ram. Singla from Madhav University; Rajasthan. He has completed 03 FDP, 15 National and International seminars/ symposia/ conferences/ workshops and presented 8 research papers, of which 4 papers had been presented in international conference. He is Reviewer in Journal of Emerging Technology and Innovative Research. He has Life time membership in IPA- Indian Physics Association (SUR/LM/13239), IAENG- International Association Engineers &amp; SDIWC- the Society of Digital Information and Wireless Communication. He has been coordinate IIRS, ISRO online programmes. His research area is Digital Electronics &amp; Microcontroller. He is also a good speaker. He has also given expert lectures in a one-week national workshop and a 3-days camp, which was sponsored by university.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has a very active and energetic dynamic personality.</p>\r\n', 10697, NULL, NULL, 'Dr__nisarg.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/Dr__nisarg.jpg', NULL),
(66, 'ANKUR MONDAL', 'JADUPATI MONDAL', '1981-04-27', '902425789', '9477367494', 'mondal.ankur@gmail.com', 'Mrs. Dipshikha Mondal', '4B/4, Urban Sabujayan Jagatipota, kolkata- 700099', 'Calcutta Public School', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', 700099, 'India', 'Ankur Mondal', 2147483647, 'SBI', 'Madurdaha Krishnakunja', 'SBIN0016639', 'AWTPM6943R', 'Anarjo', 'Ankur Mondal', 'Hindi', 'Fiction', 3, '2', '2', '<p>This is a story of so called &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;; those are not at all interested in civilized world. It is n fiction adventure, in remote jungle surrounded by hill area of some tribes. In general the tribes use their long -knife, flambeau, bow and venomous-arrow, sword, long- spear, lance, stone hammer etc for their own protection. Also they use ropes made by many creepers of jungle. They don&rsquo;t use clothes for cladding themselves. Few of them use bark or plant leaves for clothing. One mentor is always there, who is called &lsquo;Pradhan (leader) of the jungle&rsquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the present leader is not actually tribe by birth. He is a civilized, but poor human being, came here for job from North East India. He has a sister also along with him in the forest office.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is all in all to take emergency decision for welfare of jungle. He is also considered as priest of the jungle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The jungle is divided into two parts by a waterfall. One side is safe for living; another side is dense and not safe. In the living area of jungle there is a tall and huge uncut one stone, treated as The GOD of the jungle. And the worship of The GOD is done by the priest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All animals and living beings are there, in the jungle. Like- omnivorous, carnivorous, reptiles, fishes, mammals, birds etc. All are free to move unless they hurt anybody for their hunger. It is considered that all living and nonliving beings of the jungle are connected to each other directly or indirectly by the blessing of The GOD.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are some certain rules, made by the leader to keep peace in the jungle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One &lsquo;Arjo&rsquo;, (civilized) forest officer will come here and gradually he will fall in love of the jungle. He is brave heart and will save an &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;, (tribe) child from the mouth of the tiger. Then a holy &ldquo;Homa Joggo&rdquo; (sacred fire) will happen by the priest, in front of The Jungle GOD, the large stone, to destroy all evils from the jungle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that, the recent forest officer, very easily, will win the heart of everybody, even of the leader. At the end this story, the forest officer will leave the job and become the leader of the jungle. And he will build a non-paid school for tribe children, a non-paid hospital for everybody within the forest and will totally separate the jungle from the outsiders without any emergency cases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>This is a story of so called &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;; those are not at all interested in civilized world. It is n fiction adventure, in remote jungle surrounded by hill area of some tribes. In general the tribes use their long -knife, flambeau, bow and venomous-arrow, sword, long- spear, lance, stone hammer etc for their own protection. Also they use ropes made by many creepers of jungle. They don&rsquo;t use clothes for cladding themselves. Few of them use bark or plant leaves for clothing. One mentor is always there, who is called &lsquo;Pradhan (leader) of the jungle&rsquo;. All animals and living beings are there, in the jungle. Like- omnivorous, carnivorous, reptiles, fishes, mammals, birds etc. All are free to move unless they hurt anybody for their hunger. It is considered that all living and nonliving beings of the jungle are connected to each other directly or indirectly by the blessing of The GOD. In the jungle there is a tall and huge uncut one stone, treated as The GOD of the jungle. And the worship of The GOD is done by the priest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is all in all to take emergency decision for welfare of jungle. He is also considered as priest of the jungle. One &lsquo;Arjo&rsquo;, (civilized) forest officer will come here and gradually he will fall in love of the jungle. He is brave heart and will save an &lsquo;Anarjo&rsquo;, (tribe) child from the mouth of the tiger. After that, the recent forest officer, very easily, will win the heart of everybody, even of the leader. Then a holy &ldquo;Homa Joggo&rdquo; (sacred fire) will happen by the priest, in front of The Jungle GOD, (the large stone), to destroy all evils from the jungle. At the end this story, the recent forest officer will leave the job and become the leader of the jungle. This is for the welfare and protection of the jungle from the outsiders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: All the characters and events depicted are fictitious. Any similarity to a person living or dead is purely coincidental.</p>\r\n', '<p>ANKUR MONDAL, was born in a native village of West Bengal in 1981. From his very childhood he loved nature- free air, open sky, animals, birds, fishes etc. He studied, Masters in Computer Science in 2007, from WBUT, West Bengal. In his career, he has been teaching, giving training and doing some research works in different fields, related to computer science. He completed Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning certification, successfully in the year of 2019. But, at the beginning of 2020, the worldwide pandemic changed his mind totally, due to live and let live others. He started to thing several alternatives apart from AIML. He become the intense disciple of Lord Sri Sri Ramakrishna and started to realize the ultimate truth of the life. Now he tries to enlighten the spirit of the life through different type of writings.</p>\r\n', 11058, NULL, NULL, 'IMG_27411.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/IMG_27411.jpg', NULL);
