60+ thousand scholars, researchers and professors read and share his work world-wide; his works have been cited in a good number of theses and research papers, world-wide. He writes articles regularly for Kannada-monthly &lsquo;Valmiki Karnataka&rsquo;. He authored 26 books, including economics, prose, and poetry. &ldquo;Shrimad Valmiki Ramayana Maha-Kaavya Darshanm (Part-1, 2 &amp; 3)&rdquo; is his great contribution<strong>. </strong>Now his book on <strong>&ldquo;Chaitra Gali: Prema Gite&rdquo;,</strong> poems in Kannada, focuses on his own experience in love and life</p>\r\n', 8189, NULL, NULL, 'IMG-4674_(2)1.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/IMG-4674_(2)1.jpg', NULL),
(139, 'Arjun  Pangannavar', 'Yallappa', '1951-06-29', '8971171477', '9448762733', 'arjun_pangannavar@yahoo.in', 'Smt Gowramma (wife)', 'RS# 173/B/5. H # 71,Vidyanagar, GOKAK-591307', 'Opp Saibaba Mandir', 'GOKAK-591307', 'Karnataka', 591307, 'India', 'Shweta Pangannavar', 2147483647, 'State Bank of India, ', 'ADB Branch GOKAK Code-1814', 'SBIN0001814', 'ADNPP6523B', 'Chaitra Gali: Prema Gite', 'Arjun  Pangannavar', 'Hindi', 'Poetry', 1, '1', '1', '<p>Poet Arjun Y. Pangannavar&rsquo;s&nbsp; &nbsp;the book <strong>&ldquo;Chaitra Gali: Prema Gite&rdquo; comprises 53 </strong>poems in Kannada, focuses on his own experience in love and life. The book has fifty-five poems on nature, fate, life&rsquo;s different looks and stages and love&rsquo;s different faces, gifts, conversations, pleasures, longings, despairs, soothing and commemoration. These poems were composed during specific period on account of the happenings and instant feelings from stubborn and maddened heart, poems flew not from mind to write but from the bottom of heart and its instant reaction; so these poems are the memories of those events that I depicted them in form of poems, some are composed to eternalized the love and loved one, it is not the physical attraction&rsquo;s love and its feelings but soul&rsquo;s longing to one with the soul that attracted each other, love is not love that alters when finds alteration, it is the real love that has no bindings of time and purpose; the heart perception is strange, it shares its feelings, not passion, with the those whoever feels so by meets; love must be enduring but should not be erotic, meanwhile love is for all so it must also be eternalized. So are my poems, may diffuse love-honey perfume to the readers, but they are prayed not to despise them, they are my love.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>&nbsp; &ldquo;ಎಲ್ಲ 53 ಕವನಗಳನ್ನು ಅಕ್ಟೋಬರ 1977 ರಿಂದ ನವ್ಹೆಂಬರ 2021ರ ಅವಧಿಯಲ್ಲಿ ರಚಿಸಿರುತ್ತೇನೆ. ಬಾಲ್ಯದಲಿ ತಿಳುವಳಕೆ ಬಂದಾಗಿನಿಂದ ಇಲ್ಲಿವರೆಗೆ ಬದುಕಿನಲ್ಲಿ ಹಲವಾರು ಘಟನೆಗಳು ಘಟಿಸಿದವು; ಈ ಘಟನೆಗಳನ್ನು ನನ್ನನ್ನು ನಾಲ್ಕು ಸೆಳೆತಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಎಳೆದವು: ಮೊದಲನೆಯದಾಗಿ, 1957ರಿಂದ 1980ರ ವರೆಗಿನ ಬದುಕಿನ ಚೈತ್ರಗಾಳಿಯ ಅನುಭವಗಳು ನನ್ನನ್ನು ಕಿಶೋರಾವಸ್ಥೆಯ, ಯವ್ವನದ ಸ್ನೇಹ ಮೋಜು ಮಸ್ತಿ ಮುಗ್ದ ಪ್ರೇಮದ ಕನಸುಗಳ ಪರ್ವ.&rdquo; ಕವಿ ಅರ್ಜುನ ಪಂಗಣ್ಣವರರ ಈ ಮನದ ನುಡಿಯ ಅವರ ಕವನ ಕೃತಿ ʻಚೈತ್ರಗಾಳಿ:ಪ್ರೇಮಗೀತೆʼಯು ಮನುಷ್ಯನ ಬದುಕಿನಲ್ಲಿ ಬರುವ ಎಲ್ಲ ನಿರಂತರ ಪ್ರೇಮಗಳ ಕನ್ನಡಿಯಾಗಿದೆ; ಬಾಲ್ಯಾವಸ್ಥೆಯಿಂದ ಮುಪ್ಪಿನಾವಸ್ಥೆವರೆಗೂ ಸಂದರ್ಭ, ಸಮಯಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಘಟಿಸುವ ಅನಿರೀಕ್ಷಿತ ಘಟನೆಗಳು, ಅವುಗಳ ಹಿಂದಿನ ಭಾವನೆಗಳು ಮತ್ತು ಮನಸ್ಸಿನ ತುಡಿತಗಳು ʻಚೈತ್ರಗಾಳಿ: ಪ್ರೇಮಗೀತೆʼಯಲ್ಲಿ ಸೂಸಿ ಬಂದಿವೆ, ಶೀರ್ಷಕೆ ಅರ್ಥಪೂರ್ಣವಾಗಿದೆ; ಯವೌನದ ಪ್ರೇಮವು ದೇಹದ ಆಕರ್ಷಣಿಯದಾಗಿರದೇ ಎಲ್ಲ ಸಂದರ್ಭದಲ್ಲೂ, ಕಾಲದಲ್ಲೂ ನಿರಂತರ ಅತ್ಮಗಳ ಮಿಲನದ ಹಂಬಲ ಹೊಂದಿಬೇಕು. ಕವಿ ಅರ್ಜುನ ಪಂಗಣ್ಣವರರು ಈಗಾಗಲೆ ಕನ್ನಡ ಮತ್ತು ಇಂಗ್ಲೀಷಿನಲ್ಲಿ ಸಾಕಷ್ಟು ಸಾಹಿತ್ಯವನ್ನು ಕಲೆ ಮತ್ತು ಸಮಾಜ ವಿಜ್ಞಾನ ಕೇತ್ರದಲ್ಲಿ ಕೊಡುಗೆ ನೀಡಿರುವರು,ʻಚೈತ್ರಗಾಳಿ:ಪ್ರೇಮಗೀತೆʼ ಕವನ ಕೃತಿಯೂ ಓದುಗರ ಮನಮೆಚ್ಚವ ಕೃತಿಯಾಗಲೆಂದು ಶುಭಕೋರುವೆ ಮತ್ತು ಅಭಿನಂದಿಸುವೆ.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ಡಾ. ಕವಿತಾ ಕುಸುಗಲ್ಲ</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ಇಂಗ್ಲೀಷ ವಿಭಾಗ, ರಾಣಿ ಚನ್ನಮ್ಮ ವಿಶ್ವವಿದ್ಯಾಲಯ ಬೆಳಗಾವಿ</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Prof, Dr. Arjun Y Pangannavar is a versatile writer and poet in Kannada and English language. He was born on 29th June 1951 at Gokak-Falls in labor-class tribal family. Shri Yallappa Pangannavar and Smt Holhevva were his parents; He studied Economics, English and Kannada Literature at graduation level and MA &amp; PhD in economics.&nbsp; He started his lecturer career from 1977 and retired (2011) as Associated Professor of Economics and Principal (2014) from a reputed graduate-colleges. He is guide to PhD research scholars from Bharathiar University Coimbatore (TN) India&mdash;one is awarded PhD. Kannada University Hampi, Karnataka has nominated him as a member of Advisory Committee of `The Chair of Valmiki Studies&rsquo;.&nbsp; Micro-finance, women empowerment, rural development, and economic issues are the special area of his research. He has presented research papers in national and international seminars, conferences and published in national and international journals, 11 research works in ResearchGate wherein 60+ thousand scholars, researchers and professors read and share his work world-wide; his works have been cited in a good number of theses and research papers, world-wide. He writes articles regularly for Kannada-monthly &lsquo;Valmiki Karnataka&rsquo;. He authored 26 books, including economics, prose, and poetry. &ldquo;Shrimad Valmiki Ramayana Maha-Kaavya Darshanm (Part-1, 2 &amp; 3)&rdquo; is his great contribution<strong>. </strong>Now his book on <strong>&ldquo;Chaitra Gali: Prema Gite&rdquo;,</strong> poems in Kannada, focuses on his own experience in love and life</p>\r\n', 8189, NULL, NULL, 'IMG-4674_(2)2.jpg', 'https://bfcgroup.in//assets/asf_authorMail/profilePic/IMG-4674_(2)2.jpg', NULL),
